<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-20T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="490" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">671.116/26: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Rumania (<persName type="to">Owsley</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-20T13:00:00-05:00">December 20, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>32. Your despatch No. 36 November 20.<note n="48" xml:id="d490fn48">Not printed.</note> In connection with discussion of liquor
                                quota for Rumania Davila asserts that Popescu of Ministry <pb facs="0797" n="693" xml:id="pg_693"/> of Industry and Commerce
                                and other officials can now convince you of non-discriminatory
                                attitude of Rumanian Government toward allotment of import licences
                                for American products.</p>
                            <p>Please confer with appropriate officials and advise the Department
                                promptly whether Rumanians are now fulfilling in a reasonable manner
                                the assurance conveyed by the Legation’s No. 12, June 15, 6 p.m.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>